Glutathione synthetase, chloroplast precursor (EC 6.3.2.3)
(Glutathione synthase) (GSH synthetase) (GSH-S).
"cDNA cloning and expression analysis of genes encoding GSH synthesis
in roots of the heavy-metal accumulator Brassica juncea L.: evidence
for Cd-induction of a putative mitochondrial gamma-glutamylcysteine
synthetase isoform.";
-!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: ATP + gamma-L-glutamyl-L-cysteine + glycine =
    ADP + phosphate + glutathione.
-!- PATHWAY: Sulfur metabolism; glutathione biosynthesis; glutathione
    from L-cysteine and L-glutamate: step 2 [final step].
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Plastid; chloroplast (Potential).
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the eukaryotic GSH synthase family.
ATP-binding; Chloroplast; Glutathione biosynthesis; Ligase;
Nucleotide-binding; Plastid; Transit peptide.
